# README sync

The project README at `README.md` is the canonical overview of what this app is and does.

When your changes affect any of the following, update `README.md` in the same task (before finishing):

- User-facing routes, pages, or wizard steps
- Prospect funnel or advisor portal workflows
- API endpoints or auth requirements
- Supabase schema, migrations, or prospect status values
- External integrations (Calendly, Monday.com, Supabase)
- Core analysis behavior (Roth model, Monte Carlo, premium optimizer, PDF report)
- Environment variables or setup steps (also update `ENV.md` when env-related)
- Tech stack or major directory layout

Keep edits focused: change only the sections that are stale. Do not rewrite unrelated README content.

If unsure whether a change is user- or architect-facing enough to document, err on updating the README briefly rather than leaving it wrong.
